==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mouse-ear
<hw>Mouse"-ear`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The forget-me-not (<spn>Myosotis palustris</spn>) and
other species of the same genus.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A European
species of hawkweed (<spn>Hieracium Pilosella</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mouse-ear chickweed</b></col>, <cd>a name of two common
species of chickweed (<spn>Cerastium vulgarium</spn>, and <spn>Cerastium
viscosum</spn>).</cd> -- <col><b>Mouse-ear cress</b></col>, <cd>a low
cruciferous herb (<spn>Sisymbrium Thaliana</spn>). All these are low
herbs with soft, oval, or obovate leaves, whence the name.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mousefish</ent>⟦br⟧
